@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About - WebGPU Framework</PageTitle>

<div class="about-container">
	<h1>PanoramicData.Blazor.WebGpu</h1>
	<p class="lead">A comprehensive WebGPU framework for Blazor WebAssembly</p>

	<section class="about-section">
		<h2>What is WebGPU?</h2>
		<p>
			WebGPU is a modern graphics API that provides low-level, high-performance access to GPU capabilities
			directly from web browsers. It enables developers to create stunning 3D graphics, complex visualizations,
			and GPU-accelerated computations with performance approaching native applications.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="about-section">
		<h2>Framework Features</h2>
		<div class="feature-grid">
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-code"></span> C# First</h3>
				<p>Write GPU-accelerated applications using pure C# with no JavaScript knowledge required.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-layers"></span> Component-Based</h3>
				<p>Blazor components for cameras, containers, and performance metrics with automatic lifecycle management.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-flash"></span> Hot-Reload</h3>
				<p>Edit and reload WGSL shaders in real-time during development with instant validation feedback.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-dashboard"></span> Performance Metrics</h3>
				<p>Built-in FPS monitoring, frame timing, and custom metric tracking.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-camera-slr"></span> Camera System</h3>
				<p>Orbit, first-person, and orthographic cameras with automatic matrix calculations.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<h3><span class="oi oi-shield"></span> Error Handling</h3>
				<p>Comprehensive error messages and browser compatibility detection.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

